Macron&nbsp; insisted on the need for Europe to strengthen its defence. "No matter whether peace in Ukraine is reached quickly or not, European states must be able to defend themselves better > or dissuade any new action - he explained -. We have to increase our defense. We remain faithful to NATO, but we must strengthen our independence. The future of Europe must not be decided in Washington and Moscow," the French President warned. "The world continues to be more brutal, our prosperity and security have become more uncertain - said Macron launching the alarm for the increasing world insecurity and Russian danger -. Let's go into a new era. The Russian threat touches all >, who can believe it will stop?. We have to act. We can no longer believe Russia on the word," he insisted.&nbsp;
